snippet.title: Demonetisation: No More Exchange of Rs 500 and Rs 1000 Notes, Rs 1000 Notes Completely Out

localized.description:
Demonetisation: Modi government says no to exchange of Rs 500 and Rs 1000 notes. Peoples can still use old notes of Rs 500 to pay utility bills, recharge prepaid mobile numbers, school fees upto Rs 2000 in central and state government colleges. 
Peoples can deposit old notes of Rs 500 and Rs 1000 at banks and can withdraw it through cheque or ATMs.
